{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place gelatine leaves into a ceramic or glass bowl and cover with cold water. Set aside to soak until gelatine leaves have swelled and softened (approx. 5 minutes).","Place cream, milk, caster sugar and vanilla bean paste or vanilla sugar into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>6 min\/80°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Squeeze water from gelatine leaves, then add squeezed gelatine leaves to mixing bowl and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>, or until gelatine has dissolved.","Lightly brush water or cognac into 8 serving glasses or ramekins (100 -120 mL), then transfer panna cotta mixture into them. Cover each with plastic wrap and place into refrigerator to set for a minimum 6 hours.","Once set, remove from refrigerator and garnish with fresh seasonal berries to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["4 titanium strength gelatine leaves","500 g pouring (whipping) cream","250 g full cream milk","150 g caster sugar, to taste","1 tsp vanilla bean paste","1 tbsp water, for brushing","seasonal berries, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r98714","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-TMThluqxEgg\/XZaoY1yh6VI\/AAAAAAAAhJw\/CAtPn0g1KPk7gFBLI1_4bCgm-9TrrLPxACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_nmp9c3Iib_Ha4qEk.png","title":"Panna cotta","publishedAt":"2015-08-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.1 g","fat":"23.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"23.5 g","calories":"1318 kJ \/ 314 kcal"},"usefulItems":"ceramic or glass bowl, plastic wrap, 8 serving glasses, pastry brush, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Use any fresh seasonal fruit of choice to top your panna cotta or for an extra treat, drizzle over caramel sauce, chocolate ganache or a flavoured sauce of your choice."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","6h 15m","8 portion"]}